From: Gal Pressman <gal@nvidia.com>
Date: Wed, 4 Sep 2024 10:49:20 +0300
Subject: ixgbe: Remove setting of RX software timestamp
Patch-mainline: v6.12-rc1
Git-commit: 12283fad6d2ea43450a28de4394a756a401fa71c
References: jsc#PED-9961

The responsibility for reporting of RX software timestamp has moved to
the core layer (see __ethtool_get_ts_info()), remove usage from the
device drivers.

Reviewed-by: Carolina Jubran <cjubran@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Rahul Rameshbabu <rrameshbabu@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Gal Pressman <gal@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Tony Nguyen <anthony.l.nguyen@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_ethtool.c |    4 ----
 1 file changed, 4 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_ethtool.c
@@ -3196,16 +3196,12 @@ static int ixgbe_get_ts_info(struct net_
 
 	info->so_timestamping =
 		SOF_TIMESTAMPING_TX_SOFTWARE |
-		SOF_TIMESTAMPING_RX_SOFTWARE |
-		SOF_TIMESTAMPING_SOFTWARE |
 		SOF_TIMESTAMPING_TX_HARDWARE |
 		SOF_TIMESTAMPING_RX_HARDWARE |
 		SOF_TIMESTAMPING_RAW_HARDWARE;
 
 	if (adapter->ptp_clock)
 		info->phc_index = ptp_clock_index(adapter->ptp_clock);
-	else
-		info->phc_index = -1;
 
 	info->tx_types =
 		BIT(HWTSTAMP_TX_OFF) |
